    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Before it can do anything useful, LibVLC must be initialized. You can create one (or more) instance(s) of LibVLC in a given process, with <ref refid="group__libvlc__core_1ga7f1ea72f2cc4a7459ac59997599e14d1" kindref="member">libvlc_new()</ref> and destroy them with <ref refid="group__libvlc__core_1ga42f80821f3b5e2e9a1fe38c96d40ee71" kindref="member">libvlc_release()</ref>.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="version"><para>Unless otherwise stated, these functions are available from LibVLC versions numbered 1.1.0 or more. Earlier versions (0.9.x and 1.0.x) are <bold>not</bold> compatible. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
